formatted_address: 476D Upper Serangoon View, Kopitiam Corner @ Hougang Capeview, Singapore 531476
name: Pasta & Broiler Tenderfresh

reviews.text: Staff changed but food has not improved and prices still expensive. Take away also must pay extra 30 cent.

I ordered takeaway laksa prawn spaghetti, whole spring chicken with fries, crispy skin chicken chop with cream, chicken bolognese spaghetti and XL chicken cutlet cream spaghetti. Everything tastes amazing, especially the laksa sauce. The food has improved a lot. Will definitely order more often

SUPER Slow service, food ordered at 640pm but came 825pm. The cheese fries taste like uncooked fries with the sauces. The chicken mushroom PESTO pasta taste like chicken mushroom BROWN sauce pasta. The food totally not worth the wait and the price.

You have been warned.
The Happiness Set taste so~so, like spring chicken cut into small pieces. The roasted chicken is nice, the downside is too little chili sauce to dip. Will buy again.

Please hire someone with good attitude and willing to work. Your staff who take order/cashier given bad experience to the customer with her terrible attitude, sibeh dulan face that making me eating your food with fire! Although food taste not bad but I would triple consider if I would need to order food from her again.

vicinity: 476D Upper Serangoon View, Kopitiam Corner @ Hougang Capeview
